item.title: I would like a Auto CacheDownloader and how do I pack my cache?
item.dc:creator: @Get_Blitz Get Blitz
item.description:
@Get_Blitz wrote:

Download winrar

Find your cache

open the cache folder

Select everything inside the cache folder

right click “add to archive”

A box should come up and change rar to zip

Click “ok”

your done

item.title: I would like a Auto CacheDownloader and how do I pack my cache?
item.dc:creator: @imsuperman05 imsuperman05
item.description:
@imsuperman05 wrote:

Google an autocachedownloader… there’s a tutorial out there.

Packing your cache, extract it into .ZIP file, but extract THE FILES not the folder or it won’t work. Then download dropbox and put your cache into public folder and wait for the checkmark to go green, then right-click copy public link and add that into your AutoCacheDownloader.
